        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": ">> * Add syntax=legacy; make syntax=treesitter the default (if highlight queries are available)\n>\n> Given how syntax option is for selection of what syntax to use, shouldn't the method be a separate setting (e.g. syntaxmethod)?\n\nTo give a bit more context why that matters:\nPlugin [nvim-dap-disasm](https://codeberg.org/Jorenar/nvim-dap-disasm) creates a buffer with `filetype=dap-disassembly` and `syntax=asm`.  \nUsers then can [override the syntax](https://codeberg.org/Jorenar/nvim-dap-disasm/issues/10) via autocommand:\n```vim\nautocmd FileType dap-disassembly\n      \\ autocmd BufWinEnter <buffer> ++once  setl syntax=nasm\n```\n\nNow, if user will want to use treesitter for highlighting, they will set `syntax=treesitter`, but it will, as I understand, try to use grammar for `dap-disassembly`, which doesn't exists, so it will fallback to legacy method.\n\nAnd the other way around, what if treesitter doesn't handle the case well? If, as I assume, `syntax=nasm` will default to treesitter, then how is user to choose the legacy way of highlight?",
            "created_at": "2026-04-13T17:33:05Z",
